<body>
    <h1>eZ Cloud extension</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 id=3D"eZCloudextension-About">About</h1>
<p>The eZ Cloud extension is used to customize your eZ Cloud installation w=
ith various sets of parameters that can be found in the .ini file, and othe=
r types of configuration provided by this extension.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"eZCloudextension-Download">Download</h1>
<p>You can download the extension by clicking on this link: <a href=3D"http=
s://confluence.ez.no/download/attachments/16286206/ezcloud-extension-v1.0.0=
.tar.gz" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://confluence.ez.no/=
download/attachments/16286206/ezcloud-extension-v1.0.0.tar.gz</a></p>
<p>Current version: 1.0.0</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"eZCloudextension-Settings">Settings</h1>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h5 id=3D"eZCloudextension-extension/ezcloud/settings/ezcloud.ini">extensio=
n/ezcloud/settings/ezcloud.ini</h5>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>[SiteAccessSettings]
AdminList[]
AdminList[]=3Dezdemo_site_admin
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>In this block setting you need to specify the siteaccess name to your ad=
min siteaccess. This is so that eZ Cloud can put your admin interface on a =
dedicated set of machines.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>[Solr]
# Path to the custom config tarball you uploaded to the ftp
# If you don't have any custom configuration just leave empty string
CustomConfigFile=3D
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>This block should be used with caution and needs to be pre-appro=
ved by eZ Cloud team before applying them.</strong></p>
<p>In your SFTP account there is a folder called &quot;<code>solr/</code>&q=
uot;. In this folder you can upload a custom solr configuration tarball if =
you have special customizations to solr configuration.</p>
<p>The correct method of packing the solr config is as follows:</p>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>cd /path/to/solr/conf
tar zcvf ezcloud_solr_config.tar.gz schema.xml protwords.txt stopwords.txt =
synonyms.txt
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> We currently do not support changes to <code>solr=
config.xml</code>.</p>
<p>If you pack solr config using this method (assuming you upload the file =
to the <code>solr/</code> directory on sftp) the correct ini setting would =
be</p>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>[Solr]
CustomConfigFile=3Dezcloud_solr_config.tar.gz
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>[Settings]
# List of settings to enforce
#
# Syntax:
# ForceSettings[]=3D&lt;file&gt;|&lt;group&gt;|&lt;key&gt;|&lt;value&gt;
#
# Example
# ForceSettings[]=3Dsite.ini|TemplateSettings|TemplateCache|disabled
#
ForceSettings[]
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>This block should be used with caution and needs to be pre-appro=
ved by eZ Cloud team before applying them.</strong></p>
<p>This block allows the override of any setting in Exponential (even settin=
gs we modify on deployment like cache enforcement). You need to have a good=
 reason to need to set settings in this manner.</p>
<p>Note that all settings will be written to <code>settings/override/&lt;fi=
le&gt;[.append.php]</code></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"eZCloudextension-Cronjobs">Cronjobs</h1>
<p>Cronjobs in eZ Cloud are preset to run on 5 different cronjob parts, pre=
fixed with &quot;<code>ezc_</code>&quot;.</p>
<p>Here are the dates for the different parts:</p>
<ul>
<li>frequent: Every 5 minutes</li>
<li>hourly: Random minute every hour</li>
<li>nightly: Random minute between 03:00 and 03:59 (UTC+3) every night</li>
<li>daily: Random minute between 13:00 and 13:59 (UTC+3) every day</li>
<li>weekly: Random minute between 02:00 and 02:59 (UTC+3) every week at Sat=
urday</li>
</ul>
<p>The random minute is because the servers are in a shared environment to =
prevent multiple cronjobs spawning at the same time.</p>
<p>You find the parts defined in <code>extension/ezcloud/settings/cronjob.i=
ni.append.php</code>.</p>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>[CronjobSettings]
ExtensionDirectories[]=3Dezcloud

[CronjobPart-ezc_frequent]

[CronjobPart-ezc_hourly]

[CronjobPart-ezc_nightly]

[CronjobPart-ezc_daily]

[CronjobPart-ezc_weekly]

</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>This file functions like the normal <code>cronjobs.ini</code> provided b=
y Exponential.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"eZCloudextension-Apacheconfiguration">Apache configuration</h1>
<p>We also allow to add custom <code>RewriteRule</code> and <code>RewriteCo=
nd</code> as well as custom mimetypes</p>
<h5 id=3D"eZCloudextension-Customrewrites">Custom rewrites</h5>
<p>There is a file in the extension located <code>extension/ezcloud/conf/ht=
tpd/custom-rewrites.conf</code></p>
<p>All rewrite entries in this file are prepended to the top of our rewrite=
 section in the Apache configuration to make sure your custom rewrites will=
 always trigger.</p>
<p>In this file you will find a commented example on how to add rewrites. Y=
ou can copy paste the custom rewrites you need from your local apache confi=
g into this file. Note that all rewrites must start with the forward slash =
regardless of what your local version may look like, example:</p>
<p>If you have a working rewrite that looks like this:</p>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>RewriteRule ^my_custom_file.txt - [L]
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>it needs to be rewritten to look like this</p>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>RewriteRule ^/my_custom_file.txt - [L]
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>This is because we run <code>httpd</code> on RHEL and this is the syntax=
 that it requires for rewrites due to how we have setup eZ Cloud.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h5 id=3D"eZCloudextension-Custommime-types">Custom mime-types</h5>
<p>There is a file in the extension located <code>extension/ezcloud/conf/ht=
tpd/custom-mime-types.conf</code><br />In this file you can add <code>AddTy=
pe</code> entries.</p>
<p>Example:</p>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>AddType application/x-font-woff .woff
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>This would add support of <code>.woff</code> files to be of type <code>a=
pplication/x-font-woff</code> in eZ Cloud Apache configuration.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
